                        h2(id="typography") Typography
                        h3 Utility Classes
                        h4(id="typography-family") Family
                        p Type comes in three families, set by variables in <code class="docs--code-inline">assets/type.css</code>. By default, the <code class="docs--code-inline">body</code> element is set to sans.
                        .docs--example
                            .t--family-serif Serif text
                            .t--family-sans Sans text
                            .t--family-mono Monospace text
                        pre.docs--code
                            code.html.
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--family-serif&quot;&gt;Serif text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--family-sans&quot;&gt;Sans text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--family-mono&quot;&gt;Monospace text&lt;/div&gt;
                        h4(id="typography-size") Size
                        p Type comes in 5 sizes, set by a <a href="http://www.modularscale.com/">modular scale.</a> The variables that dictate each size are set in <code class="docs--code-inline">assets/type.css</code>.
                        p
                            table
                                thead
                                    tr
                                        th Variable
                                        th Description
                                        th Default
                                tbody
                                    tr
                                        td <code class="docs--code-inline">--t--base-size</code>
                                        td Base Font Size
                                        td <code class="docs--code-inline">16px</code>
                                    tr
                                        td <code class="docs--code-inline">--ms-base</code>
                                        td Basis for modular scale
                                        td <code class="docs--code-inline">1rem</code>
                                    tr
                                        td <code class="docs--code-inline">--ms-ratio</code>
                                        td Ratio of modular scale sizes
                                        td <code class="docs--code-inline">1.5</code>
                        .docs--example
                            .t--size-xxl Huge text
                            .t--size-xl XLarge text
                            .t--size-l Large text
                            .t--size-m Normal text
                            .t--size-s Small text
                        pre.docs--code
                            code.html.
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--size-xxl&quot;&gt;Huge text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--size-xl&quot;&gt;XLarge text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--size-l&quot;&gt;Large text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--size-m&quot;&gt;Normal text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--size-s&quot;&gt;Small text&lt;/div&gt;
                        h4(id="typography-weight") Weight
                        p Type comes in 3 weights, set by the variables in  <code class="docs--code-inline">assets/type.css</code>.
                        .docs--example
                            .t--weight-bold Bold text
                            .t--weight-normal Normal text
                            .t--weight-light Light text
                        pre.docs--code
                            code.html.
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--weight-black&quot;&gt;Black text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--weight-bold&quot;&gt;Bold text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--weight-normal&quot;&gt;Normal text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--weight-light&quot;&gt;Light text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--weight-thin&quot;&gt;Thin text&lt;/div&gt;
                        h4(id="typography-alignment") Alignment
                        p Alignment can be set using one of three Utility classes.
                        .docs--example
                            .t--align-left Left-aligned text
                            .t--align-center Center-aligned text
                            .t--align-right Right-aligned text
                        pre.docs--code
                            code.html.
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--align-left&quot;&gt;Left-aligned text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--align-center&quot;&gt;Center-aligned text&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div class=&quot;t--align-right&quot;&gt;Right-aligned text&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
                        h3 Elements
                        h4(id="typography-headings") Headings
                        p Headings 1-4 are available as shorthand for commonly-used size, weight, and color styles. Feel free to style these as you wish.
                        .docs--example
                            h1 Heading 1
                            h2 Heading 2
                            h3 Heading 3
                            h4 Heading 4
                        pre.docs--code
                            code.html.
                                &lt;h1&gt;Heading 1&lt;/h1&gt;
                                &lt;h2&gt;Heading 2&lt;/h2&gt;
                                &lt;h3&gt;Heading 3&lt;/h3&gt;
                                &lt;h4&gt;Heading 4&lt;/h4&gt;
                        h4(id="typography-paragraphs") Paragraphs
                        p Paragraph text is styled at the <code class="docs--code-inline">body</code> level, with the exception of the addition of <code class="docs--code-inline">margin-bottom: 1rem</code> for <code class="docs--code-inline">&lt;p&gt;</code> tags.
                        .docs--example
                            p Paragraph Text. We work with clients as partners and collaborators on the way to a shared goal. While projects vary and methods evolve, our work is always characterized by a commitment to a few fundamentals.
                        pre.docs--code
                            code.html.
                                &lt;p&gt;&#10;Paragraph Text. We work with clients as partners and collaborators &#10;on the way to a shared goal. While projects vary and methods evolve, &#10;our work is always characterized by a commitment to a few fundamentals.&#10;&lt;/p&gt;
                        h4(id="typography-lists") Lists
                        p By default, <code class="docs--code-inline">&lt;ul&gt;</code> is styled with bullets and <code class="docs--code-inline">&lt;ol&gt;</code> is styled with numerals. Additionally, there is a <code class="docs--code-inline">t--list-unstyled</code> Utility class to remove styling from any list.
                        .docs--example
